&lt;h4&gt;Motional’s Las Vegas office is located less than 10 miles from the Las Vegas strip at 730 E Pilot Road and is home to one of the largest fleets of self-driving vehicles. The city’s grid system of roads and being one of America’s “smart cities” allows for extensive research and development testing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Mission Summary:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Autonomous Vehicle (AV) Test Engineering team is responsible for validating the safety, functionality, and performance of self-driving technology through rigorous, system-level testing. As a Systems Test Engineer, you will play a hands-on role in the end-to-end verification of AV features—spanning perception, planning, and control—across virtual, closed-course, and public road environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a versatile engineer to contribute to test strategy, scenario creation, and infrastructure development. Whether your expertise lies in Hardware-in-the-Loop (HIL), synthetic simulati

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mission Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a capable and highly motivated &lt;strong&gt;Engineer for our Developer Platform&lt;/strong&gt; team to enable rapid and safe software delivery by providing a unified, efficient and reliable platform for all developers at Motional. You will join a talented team of engineers that focuses on improving the engineering experience and developer productivity of teams in Motional by providing them with the necessary tools and processes. You will collaborate closely with teams across the organization to identify pain points and drive initiatives that empower teams to deliver on Motional’s mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your main focus will be on our real-time data pipeline which enables our AVs to communicate with our cloud services such as Command Center, Over-The-Air update systems, and ride hailing partners integration.&lt;/p&gt;
